## Getting Started 

First and foremost, we will load the needed packages into our Rstudio using paccman's `p_load` function.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
pacman::p_load(sf, tidyverse)
```
:::


We can now load our data into our R environment as new data frames.


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
mpsz14_shp <- st_read(dsn="data", layer="MP14_SUBZONE_WEB_PL")
```
